## 2. Full Test List (the real ~18 test groups)

This REPLACES the 4-test placeholder seed (Description, Identification, pH, Assay).

### Typical specification tests

| # | Test | Type | Acceptance Criteria | Dept |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Description | Qualitative | A white, crystalline powder | QC |
| 2 | Solubility | Qualitative | Freely soluble in water; very slightly soluble in ethanol (95%); practically insoluble in ether | QC |
| 3A | Identification — By IR | Qualitative | IR spectrum concordant with Glycine working standard | QC |
| 3B | Identification — By chemical test | Qualitative | Resulting solution violet w/ greenish-yellow fluorescence; becomes orange then yellow; intense fluorescence remains | QC |
| 4 | Appearance of solution | Qualitative | 10.0% w/v solution in CO₂-free water clear & not more intensely coloured than reference YS7 | QC |
| 5 | pH | Quantitative (BETWEEN) | 5.9 to 6.3 | QC |
| 6 | Chlorides | Quantitative (NMT) | NMT 100 ppm | QC |
| 7 | Heavy metals | Quantitative (NMT) | NMT 10 ppm | QC |
| 8 | Sulphated ash | Quantitative (NMT) | NMT 0.1 % | QC |
| 9 | Loss on drying | Quantitative (NMT) | NMT 0.5 % | QC |
| 10 | Assay (on dried basis) | Quantitative (BETWEEN) | 98.5 % to 101.5 % | QC |
| 15 | Foreign matter | Qualitative | Should be absent in 5 gm sample | QC |
| 16 | OVI / Residual solvent (Methanol) | Quantitative (NMT) | Methanol: NMT 3000 ppm (per ICH Q3C(R8)) — outside lab | Outside |
| 17 | Ethylene oxide | Quantitative (NMT) | NMT 0.1 ppm — outside lab | Outside |

### Additional tests (customer-request only — NOT part of typical spec → `is_optional = true`)

| # | Test | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|---|
| 11 | Sieve analysis | As per customer requirement |
| 12 | Bulk Density | As per customer requirement |
| 13 | Tapped Density | As per customer requirement |

> **This is your SPEC-Template optional-test mechanism, validated by the real document.** The SPEC literally separates "Additional Tests (on customer request, this is not part of typical specification)." These three map to `is_optional = true` template tests that a batch activates via `optionalTestIds`.

### Elemental impurities by AAS (ICH Q3D) — test group #14, 10 metals

**Note the discrepancy:** the SPEC sheet lists most as generic "Lowest detection limit NMT 0.5 µg/g," but the AWS worksheet and COA carry the REAL per-element ICH Q3D limits below. **The per-element limits are the meaningful ones.**

| Metal | Class (ICH Q3D) | Real Limit (AWS/COA) |
|---|---|---|
| Lead (Pb) | I | NMT 0.5 µg/g |
| Arsenic (As) | I | NMT 0.5 µg/g |
| Mercury (Hg) | I | NMT 0.1 µg/g |
| Cadmium (Cd) | I | NMT 0.5 µg/g |
| Cobalt (Co) | IIA | NMT 5.0 µg/g |
| Vanadium (V) | IIA | NMT 10.0 µg/g |
| Nickel (Ni) | IIA | NMT 20.0 µg/g |
| Lithium (Li) | III | NMT 25.0 µg/g |
| Antimony (Sb) | III | NMT 9.0 µg/g |
| Copper (Cu) | III | NMT 30.0 µg/g |

### Microbiological parameters — test group #18

| Test | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| Bacterial endotoxin test | NMT 5 EU/g |
| Pathogen in general | Should be absent |
| TAMC (Total Aerobic Microbial Count) | NMT 10³ CFU/g |
| TYMC (Total Yeast/Mould Count) | NMT 10² CFU/g |
| Escherichia coli | Should be absent |
| Salmonella | Should be absent |
| Pseudomonas aeruginosa | Should be absent |
| Staphylococcus aureus | Should be absent |
| Coliforms | Should be absent |

