## 3. Key Calculation Formulas (from MOA / AWS)

### Assay (on dried basis)
```
% Assay = ((Vs - Vb) × M × F × 100 × 100) / (0.1 × W × (100 - %LOD))
```
- Vs = sample titrant volume (ml of 0.1 M perchloric acid)
- Vb = blank titrant volume
- M  = molarity of perchloric acid (0.1 M)
- F  = 0.00751 g of C₂H₅NO₂ per ml of 0.1 M perchloric acid (equivalence factor)
- W  = sample weight (g)
- %LOD = loss on drying result (the dried-basis correction term)
- **Worked example in real AWS → 99.72 %**

> **Reconcile:** the placeholder seed's Assay formula likely omits the `(100 - %LOD)` dried-basis correction. The real formula needs it, and it makes the Assay depend on the LOD test result.

### Sulphated ash
```
Sulphated Ash % = (Weight of residue × 100) / Weight of sample
```
Real example: 0.0004 × 100 / 1.0003 = 0.04 %

### Loss on drying
```
% LOD = (Loss in weight × 100) / Weight of sample
```
Real example: 0.0025 × 100 / 1.0004 = 0.25 %

### Elemental impurities (AAS)
```
Content (µg/g) = Content of specific element (software-calculated) × SD / W
```

