## 7. Reconciliation Checklist (to run against the Product Master)

When the Master arrives, confirm each:

- [ ] Master is the revision that PRODUCES SPEC/MOA Rev 02 (or note the mismatch)
- [ ] Test count matches (~18 groups, not 4) — Description, Solubility, ID A/B, Appearance, pH, Chlorides, Heavy metals, Sulphated ash, LOD, Assay, + AAS block (10), + Micro block (9), + Foreign matter, OVI, Ethylene oxide
- [ ] Optional tests flagged correctly: Sieve, Bulk Density, Tapped Density = `is_optional`
- [ ] Assay formula includes the `(100 - %LOD)` dried-basis correction and F = 0.00751
- [ ] Elemental limits use the per-element values (Co 5.0, V 10.0, Ni 20.0, Li 25.0, Sb 9.0, Cu 30.0; Pb/As/Cd 0.5; Hg 0.1) — NOT the generic "NMT 0.5"
- [ ] Outside-lab tests flagged: OVI/Residual solvent, Ethylene oxide (`is_outside_lab = true`)
- [ ] Shelf life: documents say raw-material shelf life 5 years; confirm the FINISHED-product shelf life used for batch expiry (batch GCN/010226: Mfg Feb 2026 → Exp Jan 2031 ≈ 60 months / 5 years)
- [ ] Product code: reconcile FG00038 (SPEC/MOA) vs GCN (AWS/ARN) dual-code convention
- [ ] CC numbering format `CC/YYYY/NNN` feeds the OI-CC decision for Epic 27